# JobsGeParser core

- Single .NET 8 minimal API in `backend/JobsGeParser/`; solution at `backend/JobsGeParser.sln`
- Read `backend/README.md` before structural changes
- DI: register in `Configuration/DependencyInjection.AddJobsGeService`; keep Program.cs thin
- Endpoints: `JobsGeParser.Endpoints`, MapGroup("api/jobs/"), extension `RegisterJobsEndpoints`
- Parsing in `Scraping/HtmlProcessor`; HTTP in `Scraping/JobsGeClient`; storage in `Data/Repo` (PostgreSQL via EF Core)
- Categories defined in appsettings JobsGeParserOptions.Categories (slug, name, listUrl, enabled)
- CategorySync runs on startup — syncs categories table from config
- Scraping runs via JobScrapeWorker — one scrape run per enabled category per tick
- Upsert by jobs.ge Id; link jobs to categories via job_categories many-to-many
- Respect DetailPageDelayMs between detail-page requests
- DbContext and Repo are scoped; use IServiceScopeFactory in hosted services
- Frontend dashboard lives in `frontend/` — separate npm project, not in the .sln
- Do not add backup .csproj files or unrelated CI workflows
